HEADWORD: Pennatula
<hw>Pen*nat"u*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
L. <plw>Pennatul⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, E. <plw>Pennatulas</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. L. <ets>penna</ets> a feather.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous species of
<gen>Pennatula</gen>, <gen>Pteroides</gen>, and allied genera of
<ord>Alcyonaria</ord>, having a featherlike form; a sea-pen. The zooids
are situated along one edge of the side branches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pennatulacea</ent>⟦br⟧
